how to = do I host a game on GitHub.io

=
=
=

I can help you with that!= Hosting a game on GitHub Pages (github.io) is a great, free way to share y= our projects.

Here is the general workflow:

  1. Create a Reposito= ry: Make a new repo on GitHub.

  2. Upload Files: Upload your game files (HTML, CSS, JS). Crucially, your main file must be= named index.ht= ml.

  3. Enable Pages: Go to Settings > P= ages and set the source to your main branch.

To help you practice this immediately, I have generated a simple "Clicker= Game" below. You can download this file, name it index.html, and upload it to a new= GitHub repository to test the hosting process.

<= !---->
Simple Clicker Game
Dec 26, 9:53 AM=
<= !---->=

Instructions to Host This Game

  1. Download: Save the code above as a file nam= ed index.html on your computer.

  2. GitHub: Go to GitHub.co= m and sign in. Click the + icon in the top right and select New repository.

  3. Cr= eate: Give your repository a name (e.g., my-first-game). Check "Public" and cli= ck Create reposito= ry.

  4. Upload: On the next screen, click the l= ink that says uplo= ading an existing file. Drag and drop your index.html file there and click Commit changes.<= /p>

  5. Settings:

      Click the Settings tab at the top of your reposi= tory page.

    • On the left sideb= ar, click Page= s.

    • Under "Branch", selec= t main (or mast= er) and click Save.

  6. Play: After a minut= e or two, refresh that Pages settings screen. You will see a bar at the top= saying "Your site is live at..." with a link to your game!
